## Principles

How decisions should be made in this project.

1. **Parse, don't validate.** Convert raw input to typed values at system boundaries. Internal code trusts its types.
2. **Validate at boundaries only.** CLI args, HTTP requests, file input, external APIs. Everything internal is already typed.
3. **Consistency within a file beats any abstract "best practice."** Match surrounding code style.
4. **No abstractions for one use case.** Wait for three real use cases before abstracting. Three similar lines beat a premature helper.
5. **Comments explain WHY, never WHAT.** If a comment restates the next line of code, delete it.
